<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-12502] ColumnIndex does not reuse buffer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-12502</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ColumnIndex&lt;/tt&gt; is supposed to be reusing its shallow entry buffer. Instead it always allocates as &lt;tt&gt;buffer&lt;/tt&gt; isn&apos;t returned &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/db/ColumnIndex.java#L227&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;from &lt;tt&gt;useBuffer&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Additionally, relying on caller to set &lt;tt&gt;buffer&lt;/tt&gt; after the call is error-prone.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
